<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="482" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,431,2042]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,575,601]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Unlike the other Chinese 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saussure" authorityYear="1892" box="[617,740,575,601]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Polemistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[617,740,575,601]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Polemistus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Maidl" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[939,1101,576,601]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Polemistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrensis">
<emphasis box="[939,1101,576,601]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">P. sumatrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lack the hypersternaulus, and have a short frontal median carina, a round or triangular labrum, and a triangular lateral teeth on clypeus. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ma et Li" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Polemistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pediflavidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">P. pediflavidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Maidl, 1925)" baseAuthorityName="Maidl" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[358,680,647,674]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Polemistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrensis">
<emphasis box="[358,518,648,673]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">P. sumatrensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Maidl, F." box="[533,672,647,674]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" pagination="376 - 390" refId="ref7837" refString="Maidl, F. (1925) Fauna sumatrensis. (Beitrag Nr. 11). Sphegidae (Hym.). Entomologische Mitteilungen, 14, 376 - 390." type="journal article" year="1925">Maidl, 1925</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: labrum round; clypeus with a strong triangular lateral tooth on each side (
<figureCitation box="[729,812,683,710]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1157,1181]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,428,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-82@8.[151,1436,417,1134]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4 Polemistus pediflavidus Ma et Li, sp. nov. (Holotype, female). a. Frontal view of head; b. Dorsal view of head; c. Dorsal view of propodeum; d. Mesopleuron; e. Dorsal view of petiole and gastral tergum I (scale line for b and d: 1 mm; for a, c and e: 1.31 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4410127/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
); gena near mandible base without rugae; underside of head coarsely coriaceous, and with fine, dense punctures, without rugae; mesoscutum without rugae posteriorly; mesopleuron coarsely coriaceous, posteriorly with dense, short, longitudinal rugae; propodeal enclosure without delimiting carina (
<figureCitation box="[357,440,791,818]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1157,1181]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,428,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-82@8.[151,1436,417,1134]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4 Polemistus pediflavidus Ma et Li, sp. nov. (Holotype, female). a. Frontal view of head; b. Dorsal view of head; c. Dorsal view of propodeum; d. Mesopleuron; e. Dorsal view of petiole and gastral tergum I (scale line for b and d: 1 mm; for a, c and e: 1.31 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4410127/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
); dorsal surface of petiole without groove (
<figureCitation box="[922,1005,791,818]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1157,1181]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,428,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-82@8.[151,1436,417,1134]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4 Polemistus pediflavidus Ma et Li, sp. nov. (Holotype, female). a. Frontal view of head; b. Dorsal view of head; c. Dorsal view of propodeum; d. Mesopleuron; e. Dorsal view of petiole and gastral tergum I (scale line for b and d: 1 mm; for a, c and e: 1.31 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4410127/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Fig. 4e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,431,2042]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">
<taxonomicName authority="(Maidl, 1925)" baseAuthorityName="Maidl" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[199,518,827,854]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Polemistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrensis">
<emphasis box="[199,359,828,853]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">P. sumatrensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Maidl, F." box="[372,510,827,854]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" pagination="376 - 390" refId="ref7837" refString="Maidl, F. (1925) Fauna sumatrensis. (Beitrag Nr. 11). Sphegidae (Hym.). Entomologische Mitteilungen, 14, 376 - 390." type="journal article" year="1925">Maidl, 1925</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is characterized as follows: labrum triangular; clypeus with small triangular lateral tooth on each side; gena near mandible with dense, sturdy, transverse rugae; underside of head distinctly coriaceous, densely, conspicuously, longitudinally rugose; mesoscutum with dense, short, longitudinal rugae posteriorly; mesopleuron finely coriaceous, not rugose posteriorly; propodeal enclosure well defined by U-shaped carina; dorsal surface of petiole with longitudinal groove medially.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="483" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,431,2042]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1007,1033]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Description</emphasis>
. Female. Body length 
<quantity box="[603,744,1007,1034]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="482" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="4.5">4.5–5.5 mm</quantity>
. Black; apical third of mandible and labrum reddish brown; palpi yellow; scape ivory to yellowish; pedicel, tegula, and forewing veins fulvous; flagellomeres I–IX beneath and flagellomere I above reddish brown; pronotal lobe ivory; legs yellowish to reddish brown except coxae black. Setae on clypeus sparse, short, silvery.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,431,2042]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">
Mandible bidentate apically, outer tooth small, inner tooth broad and truncate (
<figureCitation box="[1091,1175,1151,1178]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1157,1181]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,428,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-82@8.[151,1436,417,1134]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4 Polemistus pediflavidus Ma et Li, sp. nov. (Holotype, female). a. Frontal view of head; b. Dorsal view of head; c. Dorsal view of propodeum; d. Mesopleuron; e. Dorsal view of petiole and gastral tergum I (scale line for b and d: 1 mm; for a, c and e: 1.31 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4410127/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
). Labrum round. Clypeus flat, with fine, dense punctures, free margin nearly truncate medially, laterally with large, triangular tooth (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1157,1181]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,428,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-82@8.[151,1436,417,1134]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4 Polemistus pediflavidus Ma et Li, sp. nov. (Holotype, female). a. Frontal view of head; b. Dorsal view of head; c. Dorsal view of propodeum; d. Mesopleuron; e. Dorsal view of petiole and gastral tergum I (scale line for b and d: 1 mm; for a, c and e: 1.31 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4410127/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
). Interantennal tubercle narrow, short. Median and lower frons slightly concave, lower frons with short, slender frontal median carina (
<figureCitation box="[403,484,1259,1286]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1157,1181]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,428,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-82@8.[151,1436,417,1134]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4 Polemistus pediflavidus Ma et Li, sp. nov. (Holotype, female). a. Frontal view of head; b. Dorsal view of head; c. Dorsal view of propodeum; d. Mesopleuron; e. Dorsal view of petiole and gastral tergum I (scale line for b and d: 1 mm; for a, c and e: 1.31 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4410127/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
), densely, transversely striate medially, lateral area and median frons with contiguous, large punctures and dense, sturdy and curving rugae. Upper frons with midsize to large, dense punctures. Ocellar triangle slightly convex, with midsize, dense punctures. Vertex behind ocelli with fine, dense punctures, densely, finely, transversely striate. Gena with large, contiguous punctures, coarsely coriaceous. Head underside coarsely coriaceous, finely, densely punctate. Occipital furrow much narrowed, distinctly crenate. Inner orbital furrow narrow, marginal carina sturdy, finely crenate, inner orbits markedly convergent toward clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[1193,1274,1439,1466]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1157,1181]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,428,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-82@8.[151,1436,417,1134]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4 Polemistus pediflavidus Ma et Li, sp. nov. (Holotype, female). a. Frontal view of head; b. Dorsal view of head; c. Dorsal view of propodeum; d. Mesopleuron; e. Dorsal view of petiole and gastral tergum I (scale line for b and d: 1 mm; for a, c and e: 1.31 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4410127/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
). Outer orbital furrow narrow, marginal carina sturdy, coarsely crenate. Ratio of HW: HLD: HLF = 71: 34: 68; HW: EWd: IOW: EW: OOW: TW: OCW: EL = 71: 18: 3: 25: 1: 17: 1: 62; AOD: WAS: IAD = 3: 6: 6; POD: OOD: OCD = 9: 9: 13. Length of scape: of pedicel: of flagellomere I: width of flagellomere I: length of flagellomere II: width of flagellomere II = 28: 6: 6: 5.5: 6: 6.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,431,2042]" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">
Pronotal collar incomplete, with just lateral corner. Mesoscutum coarsely coriaceous, with contiguous, midsize punctures, anterior slope nearly vertical and very high; admedian line impressed, extending to one fourth of mesoscutum length; notaulus shallowly grooved and crenate, reaching one third of mesoscutum length; parapsidal line slightly impressed. Scutellum coarsely coriaceous, with midsize, dense punctures. Metanotum coarsely coriaceous, finely, densely punctate. Mesopleuron coarsely coriaceous, with midsize to large, dense punctures, posteriorly with dense, short, slender, longitudinal rugae, scrobal sulcus shiny, omaulus and episternal sulcus distinctly crenate, hypersternaulus lacking (
<figureCitation box="[432,516,1835,1862]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1157,1181]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,428,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-82@8.[151,1436,417,1134]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4 Polemistus pediflavidus Ma et Li, sp. nov. (Holotype, female). a. Frontal view of head; b. Dorsal view of head; c. Dorsal view of propodeum; d. Mesopleuron; e. Dorsal view of petiole and gastral tergum I (scale line for b and d: 1 mm; for a, c and e: 1.31 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4410127/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
). Propodeal enclosure without delimiting carina, medially with sturdy reticulation, laterally with sparse, slender, oblique longitudinal rugae (
<figureCitation box="[802,885,1871,1898]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1157,1181]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,428,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-82@8.[151,1436,417,1134]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4 Polemistus pediflavidus Ma et Li, sp. nov. (Holotype, female). a. Frontal view of head; b. Dorsal view of head; c. Dorsal view of propodeum; d. Mesopleuron; e. Dorsal view of petiole and gastral tergum I (scale line for b and d: 1 mm; for a, c and e: 1.31 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4410127/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
); posterior surface with narrow groove medially, shiny, sides of groove large, nearly smooth, with fine, sparse punctures and some inconspicuous striae or finely coriaceous (
<figureCitation box="[260,342,1943,1970]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1157,1181]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,428,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-82@8.[151,1436,417,1134]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4 Polemistus pediflavidus Ma et Li, sp. nov. (Holotype, female). a. Frontal view of head; b. Dorsal view of head; c. Dorsal view of propodeum; d. Mesopleuron; e. Dorsal view of petiole and gastral tergum I (scale line for b and d: 1 mm; for a, c and e: 1.31 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4410127/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
), laterally and posteriorly irregularly reticulate. Lateral surface of propodeum with dense, sturdy, longitudinal rugae except irregularly rugose ventrally and reticulate posteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,431,2042]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,393]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="483" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">
Petiole short, slightly longer than wide, dorsal surface shiny, smooth (
<figureCitation box="[980,1062,2015,2042]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1157,1181]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,428,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-82@8.[151,1436,417,1134]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4 Polemistus pediflavidus Ma et Li, sp. nov. (Holotype, female). a. Frontal view of head; b. Dorsal view of head; c. Dorsal view of propodeum; d. Mesopleuron; e. Dorsal view of petiole and gastral tergum I (scale line for b and d: 1 mm; for a, c and e: 1.31 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4410127/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="482">Fig. 4e</figureCitation>
). Gastral segments half mat, with fine, dense punctures, finely coriaceous. Gaster somewhat constricted between segments I and II. Pygidial area lacking.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,393]" box="[199,389,223,249]" pageId="8" pageNumber="483">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
